        "headline":"Sharp focus on good customer service",
        "body":"<p><strong>In June 2012, we bought a Sharp microwave from a local retailer. It worked well until this month when it explicably seemed to cause all the power points in the kitchen to fail. We called in an electrician, who confirmed that it was the microwave that was causing the problem.</strong></p><p><strong>The next day, on the advice of the retailer, we contacted Sharp. Without hesitation the customer care assistant accepted everything I said and agreed to replace the appliance with the updated version of the same model, even though it was already four months out of guarantee.</strong></p><p><strong>We had to pay a £24 \"logistics fee\" but it was delivered just three days after the problem had first emerged. We are very impressed. </strong><em>BA, Hyde, Cheshire</em></p><p>That is indeed impressive service, so a big \"well done\" to Sharp – a firm we get very few complaints about.</p><p>Other happy readers this week include a Brabantia bin owner who had a new lid sent free of charge for an out of warranty bin. This is one of several letters we have received in praise of the firm.</p><p>Eurotunnel also won praise from a reader who received a refund of their return ticket and a free future crossing after they endured a five-hour wait to cross the channel.</p><p>Lastly, however, spare a thought for a reader, ZK, who took her MacBookPro Retina laptop back to PC World only to be told that \"if it was a day out of warranty\" they could not do anything without charge. ZK's broke down 30 days after the warranty expired.</p><p>Apple told her it would have replaced the logic board if she had bought it directly from them.  </p><p><strong>We welcome letters but cannotanswer individually. Email us at </strong><a href=\"mailto:consumer.champions@theguardian.com\" title=\"consumer.champions@theguardian.com\"><strong>consumer.champions@theguardian.com</strong></a><strong> or write to Consumer Champions, Money, the Guardian, 90 York Way, London N1 9GU. Please incl